          </table></p><p>RESOURCE DEL</p><p>The change in the resource element of the DEL of &#x00A3;578,941,000 arises from a &#x00A3;220,452,000 decrease in the voted element of the resource DEL and an increase of &#x00A3;799,393,000 in the non-voted element of the resource DEL mainly to the Department's non-departmental public bodies.</p><p>Voted Resource DEL</p><p>The &#x00A3;220,452,000 decrease in the voted element of the resource DEL arises from a &#x00A3;522,929,000 decrease in RfR1; from the movement of &#x00A3;312,996,000 to non-Voted Resource DEL; the movement of &#x00A3;44,370,000 to voted capital grants and &#x00A3;208,000 to non-voted capital; the decrease in Voted provision as a result of receiving Voted Appropriations in Aid (A-in-A) of &#x00A3;259,638,000 towards the Higher Education Funding Council for England's Non-Voted expenditure: the net transfer to the Department of Health of &#x00A3;4,372,000 for the</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_88ws' title='Col. 88WS &mdash; HC Deb 05 March 2004 vol 418 c88WS' name='column_88ws' href='#column_88ws' rel='bookmark'>88WS</a><p>This document provides details of Waterways Ireland's activities, its performance, and its expenditure for that year.</p>
